{"questionId":"23330049","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Helen and Jane both commence new jobs each starting on an annual salary of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mn>70</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>000</mn></math>. At&nbsp;the start of each new year, Helen receives an annual salary increase of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mn>2400</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><msub><mi>H</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> represent Helen’s annual salary at the start of her <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>th year of employment.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>At the start of each new year, Jane receives an annual salary increase of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of her previous&nbsp;year’s annual salary.</p>\n<p>Jane’s annual salary, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><msub><mi>J</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math>, at the start of her <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>th year of employment is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>J</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>70</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>03</mn></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>J</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> follows a geometric sequence, state the value of the common ratio, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>03</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[1</strong><strong>&nbsp;mark]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"23330049","referenceCode":"EXN.2.SL.TZ0.7b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that Jn follows a geometric sequence, state the value of the common ratio, r.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.4—Financial apps – compound int, annual depreciation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}